We apologize for the inconvenience, but there will be NO Devices available until TUESDAY!!!
Our Tech Department is working overtime to get those ready for us.

All leftover devices, the ones we will be using for a second family device, will be available on Wednesday morning at 8:30. Wednesday’s second device pick-up will be on a first come basis, and we are not taking phone holds.
Please check your Class Tag announcement for additional information.

post_text:
💻 Thank you for a great drive-thru, first day of school. We appreciate your commitment to your child’s education 📖.
We apologize for running out of devices and have changed plans for Wednesday device pickup.

We still have a lot of families who were not able to get their first device today, and we will need to allow them to check those out on Wednesday. We will not have second devices ready until Friday now.
So, just to recap- Wednesday, starting at 8:30 AM, in front of the office, we will be ready with more devices for only the families who still need to pick up their first device. We will set up again on Friday, at 8:30 AM, and allow families to pickup a second device.

Thank you for your patience!

Humboldt Unified School District
July 31 at 5:30 PM ·

We received confirmation that Sparklight has extended their discounted internet package.

"The company will continue to make available its 15 Mbps residential internet plan for $10 per month for the first three months of service to help low income families and those most impacted from coronavirus challenges, such as seniors and college students through December 31, 2020. Sparklight is also extending access to free public WiFi hotspots across its footprint through the end of the year in order to keep individuals and communities connected during the crisis."

Please contact Sparklight with questions you may have regarding this service at 877-692-2253.

Answered prayers! 🙏🏽 Cooper was hit by a truck last Friday and suffered a lot of pain with his injuries. He was released from the hospital last night!!!
Cooper, we’re so glad you’re healing!!! We look forward to seeing you in August. ❤️❤️❤️

“Cooper is healing wonderfully. Plastics say no skin graft. They also said no other fractures but want him to wear a boot due to the severity of the sprain on his ankle... he’ll start physical therapy up in prescott and he’ll have to come back down to phx in 2 weeks for follow ups on his burn and track physical therapy improvements.”

post_text:
Next week, May 18-20, is the last week of school! This is definitely not how we wanted to end the school year, but we are looking forward to seeing you as you drop off and pick up materials.
Last week of school open hours: May 18-20 (M/T/W), 8:00-4:00.

Next week Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday the gym will be set up for parents/students to drop off assignments, books and devices. Students will also be able to pick up personal items that were left in their desks. Tables are set up by grade level and by teacher so that you can easily find what you need.
- Yearbooks will not be ready until later this summer.
- Please be careful to social distance as needed!

post_text: Please keep an eye out for students at bus stops, at crosswalks and when driving down the street.
shared_text:
SIGNALSAZ.COM
Caution: Students Walking in Low Light Conditions | Signals AZ

Humboldt Unified School District
December 10, 2019 at 5:30 PM ·

Please remember that when it is dark in the morning it is hard to see our students waiting at bus stops. Please dress your students in light colored clothes or have reflective tape on their backpacks.

Drivers please slow down and drive with caution. It is hard to see the kids early in the morning, especially when we have had foggy mornings. Let's all do our part to keep everyone safe!

post_text: Thank you Mayor Palguta! We appreciate you looking out for our kids and the community. 🙌🏽
shared_text:
Mayor Kell Palguta
November 19, 2019 at 2:06 PM ·

Today Staff and I met with Superintendent Dan Streeter to discuss the pedestrian safety plan for the intersection of Lakeshore Dr. and Lake Valley Rd. After completion of a traffic study that was ordered this past summer it is determined that the Town will install four traffic control devices as pictured. Although a sign or a painted crosswalk can not physically stop a car but rather bring attention to pedestrians attempting to cross the road. As drivers, please be vigilant while driving on our roads.
text:
Thank you Mayor Palguta! We appreciate you looking out for our kids and the community. 🙌🏽

Mayor Kell Palguta
November 19, 2019 at 2:06 PM ·

Today Staff and I met with Superintendent Dan Streeter to discuss the pedestrian safety plan for the intersection of Lakeshore Dr. and Lake Valley Rd. After completion of a traffic study that was ordered this past summer it is determined that the Town will install four traffic control devices as pictured. Although a sign or a painted crosswalk can not physically stop a car but rather bring attention to pedestrians attempting to cross the road. As drivers, please be vigilant while driving on our roads.

post_text:
Liberty Family,
Thank you for the concern you have shown today for our students. There was a biking incident this morning at the corner of Lakeshore and Skoog near the library. Our student is doing well and was released at the scene.

Parents and guardians, please take some time with your student tonight to discuss and review safety precautions when crossing any street or intersection. Our children need to constantly focus on safety.

Again, thank you for looking out for our children, and we are so glad our student is safe and will be back to school soon.

Humboldt Unified School District
October 30, 2019 at 9:28 AM ·

Parents, please take a moment to complete the survey to help us better serve you and your students.

HUSD Parent Survey-English - As part of its dedication to ensuring that all children receive a comprehensive, world-class education, we are inviting parents to fill out a survey to see how our schools are doing. Simply follow the link, and it will take you to the survey where you will indicate the school for which you are taking the survey, and a series of questions where you will be able to rate how your child's school is doing.
